.TH std::putchar 3 "2018.03.28" "http://cppreference.com" "C++ Standard Libary"
.SH NAME
std::putchar \- std::putchar

.SH Synopsis
   Defined in header <cstdio>
   int putchar( int ch );

   Writes a character ch to stdout. Internally, the character is converted to unsigned
   char just before being written.

   Equivalent to putc(ch, stdout).

.SH Parameters

   ch - character to be written

.SH Return value

   On success, returns the written character.

   On failure, returns EOF and sets the error indicator (see ferror()) on stdout.

.SH Example

   
// Run this code

 #include <cstdio>
  
 int main()
 {
     for (char c = 'a'; c != 'z'; c++)
         std::putchar(c);
     std::putchar('\\n');
  
     // putchar return value is not equal to the argument
     int r = 0x1070;
     std::printf("\\n0x%x\\n", r);
     r = std::putchar(r);
     std::printf("\\n0x%x\\n", r);
 }

.SH Output:

 abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxy
 0x1070
 p
 0x70

